  "implementation_notes": {
    "layering": "To construct the character, use a parent container with relative positioning. Render the body image first, then place the hair and outfit images using absolute positioning (top: 0, left: 0) with identical dimensions so they perfectly overlay the base body.",
    "animation": "Cycle through body_idle, body_walk_a, and body_walk_b to create a walking animation sprite. Use 2-4 frames per second to mimic a cute, choppy walk cycle.",
    "recoloring": "For hair overlays, if the asset is neutral or grayscale, apply a tintColor in React Native Image style to dynamically change hair colors.",
    "room_setup": "Use room_bg as a fixed or scrollable background. Overlay isometric furniture assets on top, sorting their z-index dynamically based on their simulated 'Y' coordinate to ensure items placed closer to the bottom of the screen overlap items further up."
  }
